One of the significant findings from this study is that the Cs/CGQDs coated on gold thin film enhanced the sensitivity in the detection of the Hg2+ ion. The shift of resonance angle (
                              Δ
                              θ
                           ) has been introduced as a parameter to measure the sensitivity of the sensor. The shift of resonance angle (
                              Δ
                              θ
                           ) has been calculated by finding the difference between resonance angle (
                              θ
                              )
                            of different concentration mercury ion and deionized water (0 ppm represent deionized water). Table 3
                            shows the resonance angle (
                              θ
                           ) and shift of resonance angle for different concentration of Hg2+ solution in contact of gold/Cs/GQDs thin film.
